Sure, here are some example sentences in Serbian that use the word "stajati" in different forms and positions:

1. *Stojim* na autobuskoj stanici već sat vremena. (I have been *standing* at the bus stop for an hour.)
2. Jutros sam *stajao* u redu za hleb. (This morning, I *was standing* in line for bread.)
3. *Stajali* smo pored puta i gledali zalazak sunca. (We *were standing* by the road and watching the sunset.)
4. Knjiga koju tražiš *stoji* na polici iznad kreveta. (The book you're looking for *is standing* on the shelf above the bed.)
5. Ova kuća *stoji* na vrhu brda. (This house *stands* on top of a hill.)
6. Ne znam koliko novca *stoji* taj televizor. (I don't know how much that TV *costs*.)
7. Mesto na kojem *stoji* crkva je veoma staro. (The place where the church *is situated* is very old.)
8. *Stajalo* je napisano u knjizi da će se to dogoditi. (It *was stated* in the book that it would happen.)

I hope these examples help!